result.execSummary:
The defendant Latoya Dennen Jones was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Latoya Dennen Jones is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Latoya Dennen Jones was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Statements made as to Sentencing by both counsel and Defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:    COURT ORDERED Defendant to serve 10 DAYS, STRAIGHT TIME, in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 2 days time served.    Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.

*  NO ELECTRIONIC MONITORING.
